### Describe the feature

Grab and save the meeting transcription into a JSON or Markdown file

### Motivation

The current MS transcriptions are rarely useful, since they're only accessible to the meeting organiser.

I'd like to save every meeting's transcription (for every meeting I join) in a file for my local notes.

I've created a script (well, adapted it from https://github.com/akaihola/teams-transcript-scraper/blob/master/scraper.js) that grabs them, the only pointer I need is - how do I hook it up into the "on call leave" event?

### Alternatives

_No response_

### Additional context

The JS (to be pasted into the dev console):

```
async function extractTranscription() {
    // Get the meeting title
    const meetingTitle = document.querySelector('h2[data-tid="chat-title"] span')?.textContent.trim() || 'Teams Meeting';
    const content = document.querySelector('[data-tid="closed-caption-v2-virtual-list-content"]');
    if (!content) {
        console.log('content element not found');
        return;
    }

    const chatItems = content.querySelectorAll('[data-tid="closed-caption-chat-message"]');

    let listContent = "";
    chatItems.forEach(chatItem => {
        const header = chatItem.querySelector('.ui-chat__message__author').textContent;
        const message = chatItem.querySelector('[data-tid="closed-caption-text"]').textContent;

        listContent += `${header}: ${message}\n`;
    })

    return { content: listContent, title: meetingTitle };
}

function downloadMarkdown(content, filename) {
    const blob = new Blob([content], { type: 'text/markdown' });
    const link = document.createElement('a');
    link.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    link.download = filename;
    link.click();
    URL.revokeObjectURL(link.href);
}

const { content, title } = await extractTranscription();
console.log(content);  // Still log the content to the console

// Download the content as a Markdown file
const safeTitle = title.replace(/[<>:"/\\|?*\x00-\x1F]/g, '').replace(/^\.+/, '').replace(/\.+$/, '').trim();
const maxLength = 251; // 255 - 4 characters for '.md'
const safeTitleLimited = safeTitle.slice(0, maxLength);
downloadMarkdown(content, `${safeTitleLimited || 'Teams_Meeting'}.md`);
```

